/ About Section
%section.success
  .container
    .row
      .col-lg-2.col-md-2.col-xs-2
        %img.me{:alt => "", :src => '/imgs/me.jpg', width: '300px'}/
      .col-lg-8.col-lg-offset-2
        %p
          I am currently a Ph.D. student with the Department of Computing,
          Imperial College London under the supervision of Dr. Stefanos Zafeiriou and
          Dr. Bjoern Schuller. 
        %p 
          During the course of my Ph.D. I worked on 
          deep component analysis techniques for many face related applications.
          I worked on problems including face clustering, alignment, 3D
          face reconstruction, and temporal alignment of time-series.
          In 2016 I was an intern with the Google Brain team where
          I worked on
          %a{style: "color:black;text-decoration:underline", href: "https://papers.nips.cc/paper/6254-domain-separation-networks"} domain adaptation and 3D pose estimation.
          I am also lucky enough to be a recipient of the prestigious
          %a{style: "color:black;text-decoration:underline", href: "https://research.googleblog.com/2017/04/announcing-2017-google-phd-fellows-for.html"} Google Fellowship in Machine Perception, Speech Technology and Computer Vision.

%section#papers
  .container
    .row
      .col-lg-12.text-center
        %h2 Articles
        %hr.star-primary/
    .row
      .col-lg-2.col-xd-4.col-md-4
      .col-lg-8.col-xd-8.col-md-8
        {{ paper.is_article }}
        {% for paper in site.data['papers'] %}
        {% if paper.is_article == true %}
        {% include paper.html paper=paper %}
        {% endif %}
        {% endfor %}
    .row
      .col-lg-12.text-center
        %h2 Conference Publications
        %hr.star-primary/
    .row
      .col-lg-2.col-xd-4.col-md-4
      .col-lg-8.col-xd-8.col-md-8
        {% for paper in site.data['papers'] %}
        {% if paper.is_article == false%}
        {% include paper.html paper=paper %}
        {% endif %}
        {% endfor %}

